03:02.420 --> 03:05.505
VIOLET: <i>There are many people
who feel the justice system</i>

03:05.581 --> 03:09.416
<i>is rigged against them,
and sometimes it actually is.</i>

03:09.493 --> 03:12.661
<i>Yes, most police officers
are proud citizens</i>

03:12.698 --> 03:14.999
<i>who truly want to protect the public,</i>

03:15.036 --> 03:16.331
<i>but there are a few</i>

03:16.368 --> 03:19.241
<i>who will lie, cheat, and steal</i>

03:19.278 --> 03:21.264
<i>for their own interests,
and those are the ones</i>

03:21.301 --> 03:24.489
<i>who are responsible for so
many wrongful convictions.</i>

03:24.769 --> 03:27.631
On this week's episode
of <i> Until Proven Innocent,</i>

03:27.668 --> 03:28.861
we will tell the story

03:28.898 --> 03:30.506
of one corrupt cop

03:30.615 --> 03:34.349
and our attempt to bring him down.

03:34.535 --> 03:36.105
May I help you?

03:36.371 --> 03:38.779
Uh, I'm looking for a lawyer.

03:38.897 --> 03:40.806
Sometimes a ninja is more effective.

03:40.912 --> 03:42.814
Whatever gets my brother out of jail.

03:43.009 --> 03:44.248
Oh, to get your brother out of jail?

03:44.285 --> 03:45.558
Yeah, you need a lawyer. Come on.

03:45.595 --> 03:47.035
- Come with me.
- MAN: <i>I just read that you got</i>

03:47.037 --> 03:48.370
arrested for contempt, and I thought

03:48.372 --> 03:49.486
you'd be the perfect person

03:49.523 --> 03:51.650
- to take a look at my brother's case.
- Why?

03:51.736 --> 03:53.960
The same detective that
railroaded your client

03:53.997 --> 03:55.431
did the same thing to my brother.

03:55.798 --> 03:56.904
Falcone?

03:56.941 --> 03:58.392
What happened to your brother?

03:58.517 --> 04:00.410
He was blamed for bombing a synagogue

04:00.447 --> 04:03.062
15 years ago,
which he had nothing to do with.

04:03.932 --> 04:06.230
There was no evidence
tying him to the scene.

04:06.267 --> 04:07.634
What was the prosecution's theory

04:07.671 --> 04:08.986
for why he'd blow up a synagogue?

04:09.023 --> 04:11.509
That's where it gets
a little complicated.

04:11.689 --> 04:15.575
Um, my brother is Ronnie Petersen.

04:17.728 --> 04:19.228
MADELINE: Yeah, we know this case.

04:19.541 --> 04:21.091
Your brother's a white supremacist.

04:21.189 --> 04:23.140
H-He <i> was</i> a white supremacist,

04:23.234 --> 04:24.625
but he isn't like that anymore.

04:24.709 --> 04:26.024
He's totally reformed.

04:26.087 --> 04:28.671
And, most importantly,
he didn't bomb that synagogue.

04:28.747 --> 04:31.030
Falcone pinned it on Ronnie
because he wouldn't help him.

04:31.067 --> 04:32.967
Nick, man, you seem like a nice guy,

04:32.994 --> 04:34.726
but I don't know if you noticed...
I'm a black man

04:34.804 --> 04:36.947
in these here United States of America.

04:37.030 --> 04:39.323
So why would I even touch your case?

04:39.694 --> 04:41.391
Every lawyer that I've ever spoken to

04:41.428 --> 04:42.643
has kicked me out in minutes.

04:42.823 --> 04:45.345
But I just thought, since you
lost it in court over Falcone,

04:45.382 --> 04:47.389
you might want to hear
how he framed Ronnie.

04:47.593 --> 04:50.167
Falcone paid three people

04:50.285 --> 04:51.764
to say my brother was the bomber.

04:51.801 --> 04:54.327
We appreciate you coming in.
But, reformed or not,

04:54.385 --> 04:56.211
we're not in the white
supremacist business.

04:56.248 --> 04:58.006
Neither is my brother.

04:58.374 --> 05:00.770
I mean, he hates who he was.

05:00.897 --> 05:02.509
Even now, he is trying to change

05:02.546 --> 05:04.589
the way that those
guys think in prison,

05:04.609 --> 05:07.065
and he is constantly getting
his ass kicked for it.

05:07.102 --> 05:08.561
It breaks my heart.

05:13.974 --> 05:15.936
People thought you were
a sex-crazed Satanist,

05:15.973 --> 05:17.195
but you weren't.

05:17.264 --> 05:19.988
Everyone deserves a second chance,

05:20.116 --> 05:23.114
especially the ones who
regret their bad choices.

05:24.616 --> 05:26.193
Please, just look at it.

05:27.043 --> 05:28.205
CROWD: <i>White power!</i>

05:28.316 --> 05:29.731
<i>America first! White power!</i>

05:29.801 --> 05:31.967
America first! White power!

05:32.086 --> 05:34.528
America first! White power!

05:34.565 --> 05:36.899
America first! White power!

05:37.233 --> 05:38.732
<i>White power!</i>

05:38.996 --> 05:41.054
RONNIE: <i>We need to
take this country back!</i>

05:41.091 --> 05:42.256
<i>Purify our nation!</i>

05:42.682 --> 05:44.006
<i>White pow...</i>

05:44.043 --> 05:46.373
So, after we free
Ronnie, can we can try

05:46.400 --> 05:48.312
to posthumously exonerate Himmler?

05:48.349 --> 05:50.676
Nick swears his brother
is reformed now.

05:50.790 --> 05:52.926
I don't know, maybe miracles do happen.

05:52.965 --> 05:54.547
But, yes, it's hard to believe.

05:54.584 --> 05:56.181
Plus, it wouldn't be
a good look for us.

05:56.340 --> 05:58.476
Even if he did change somehow,
people wouldn't get it.

05:58.873 --> 06:00.313
That being said,

06:00.387 --> 06:03.168
finding a way to expose
Falcone is music to my ears.

06:03.293 --> 06:06.168
You guys, we can find another
case to go after Falcone for,

06:06.417 --> 06:07.967
if we really want to nail him.

06:08.004 --> 06:10.277
We're not actually entertaining
this, are we?

06:10.314 --> 06:12.842
Under normal circumstances,
I wouldn't touch this case.

06:12.879 --> 06:15.221
It's the wrongfully convicted
part that has my attention.

06:15.887 --> 06:18.180
Justice is justice, right?

06:18.559 --> 06:21.284
Yeah, as a white man,
I think maybe I should just shut up.

06:21.379 --> 06:24.371
- Maybe we just meet with him.
- Why? For what?

06:24.600 --> 06:25.816
For them.

06:28.415 --> 06:30.857
These are Falcone's corrupt
cases, right?

06:31.082 --> 06:33.684
More than half of them relied
on his paid-off witnesses,

06:33.721 --> 06:36.834
and, unfortunately,
none of them are anywhere near

06:36.871 --> 06:38.328
as obviously corrupt as this one.

06:38.418 --> 06:39.901
Yep, and, in this
case, the only evidence

06:39.938 --> 06:41.060
that's convicting Petersen

06:41.097 --> 06:42.930
is the false eyewitness testimony.

06:42.957 --> 06:44.942
So if we get one of those
witnesses to recant,

06:44.979 --> 06:47.070
we have a direct line
to taking Falcone down.

06:47.207 --> 06:48.600
What happened to shutting up?

06:48.754 --> 06:50.059
It would just be a meeting, Vi.

06:50.096 --> 06:51.793
Exactly. No promises.

06:51.928 --> 06:53.273
Madeline and I will meet with him.

06:53.301 --> 06:55.246
If he doesn't check out, we'll move on.

07:01.621 --> 07:03.392
RONNIE: <i>Well,
I didn't blow up anything.</i>

07:04.047 --> 07:05.811
I swear to you.

07:06.043 --> 07:07.633
Never did it.

07:07.732 --> 07:09.521
Your brother's theory
is that the witnesses

07:09.558 --> 07:12.121
who testified against you
were set up by a dirty cop.

07:12.158 --> 07:13.991
That's exactly what happened.

07:15.254 --> 07:17.573
And I was... easy to frame,

07:17.610 --> 07:19.254
because I was,

07:19.543 --> 07:21.941
you know, part of the
organization that did this.

07:22.277 --> 07:24.413
But I don't associate
with those people anymore.

07:24.531 --> 07:26.129
Turned my back on all that.

07:26.207 --> 07:27.497
What brought the change of heart?

07:27.534 --> 07:28.976
[EXHALES, MUTTERS]

07:29.106 --> 07:31.865
I was just so... young and stupid

07:31.902 --> 07:33.481
when I got sucked into it.

07:33.527 --> 07:36.520
These guys, they made me think
that my anger was justified.

07:36.637 --> 07:37.760
Mm.

07:37.797 --> 07:40.837
That my family was poor
because of Jews and...

07:41.730 --> 07:43.340
black people.

07:44.160 --> 07:46.535
Couple years locked up in here,

07:46.625 --> 07:48.959
started realizing how wrong I'd been.

07:48.996 --> 07:51.621
All that hate I'd spewed
at my little brother.

07:53.499 --> 07:55.343
I'm just...

07:56.473 --> 07:59.192
I just thank God Nick never
got caught up in that.

07:59.508 --> 08:01.814
I just wish I could
have those years back.

08:02.097 --> 08:03.746
You know? But I...

08:03.999 --> 08:07.387
I spilled the milk
and made a mess and...

08:08.340 --> 08:11.405
[SIGHS] ...now I got to
try my best to clean it up.

08:14.785 --> 08:16.799
My name is Easy Boudreau.

08:16.959 --> 08:19.582
I'm born and bred on
the bayous of Louisiana.

08:19.619 --> 08:21.199
If we take your case,

08:21.246 --> 08:22.416
I'd be sitting first chair,

08:22.453 --> 08:24.052
if that's okay with you.

08:26.473 --> 08:29.068
I am more than okay with
that, Mr. Boudreau.

08:29.204 --> 08:31.463
It would be a downright honor.

08:33.754 --> 08:35.818
I'm Madeline Scott.

08:35.936 --> 08:37.340
I'm just a white woman.

08:37.433 --> 08:38.970
That okay, too?

08:41.884 --> 08:44.539
Ah, gosh, this blows my mind.

08:44.746 --> 08:46.236
The people who should hate me the most

08:46.330 --> 08:49.331
are actually the ones
who are embracing me now.

08:50.201 --> 08:52.150
It really is beautiful.

08:52.714 --> 08:56.522
And I am so grateful that you
came here and heard me today.

08:59.068 --> 09:01.468
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

09:04.349 --> 09:06.169
He have any intel on Ronnie?

09:06.206 --> 09:08.812
Well, he's been here a long time.

09:08.849 --> 09:11.186
From what he tells me, Ronnie is legit.

09:11.568 --> 09:14.034
Maybe a leopard can change its spots.

09:14.887 --> 09:17.322
So, could be worth it to try
to get those other people out?

09:17.409 --> 09:19.492
I don't know,
but I guess we'll find out.

09:19.793 --> 09:21.789
<i>Violet, I'm with you 100%.</i>

09:21.826 --> 09:22.898
I don't like it.

09:22.935 --> 09:24.036
But we have a real shot

09:24.073 --> 09:25.552
at getting a bunch of these people out.

09:25.589 --> 09:27.592
You won't handle an abortion case,

09:27.629 --> 09:29.732
but you'll represent
a white supremacist?

09:29.769 --> 09:31.212
People can change.

09:31.458 --> 09:33.622
Some even deserve
redemption and forgiveness.

09:33.659 --> 09:35.966
You and I both know that
that kind of hate runs deep.

09:36.110 --> 09:38.747
Redemption only happens
when you actually repent.

09:38.966 --> 09:40.945
- He's conning you.
- You may be right.

09:40.982 --> 09:42.775
He was awful. Maybe he still is.

09:42.812 --> 09:44.863
But maybe we have to live with
that for the greater good.

09:44.925 --> 09:46.488
It's a public display
of our principles.

09:46.533 --> 09:49.011
We fight for the innocent,
no matter who they are.

09:49.192 --> 09:50.638
He may have a horrible past,

09:50.675 --> 09:51.972
but he may also be innocent.

09:52.009 --> 09:54.318
So what about Charlottesville
and all of the other

09:54.355 --> 09:56.255
hateful white supremacist
rallies that are happening

09:56.274 --> 09:57.523
all over this country?

09:57.629 --> 10:00.062
It's not interesting, Easy. It's wrong.

10:00.369 --> 10:02.475
This man does not deserve our time

10:02.512 --> 10:03.678
- or our talents.
- EASY: I hear you,

10:03.715 --> 10:05.605
but being a hothead
won't change the world.

10:05.808 --> 10:07.842
We have an opportunity
to do something big.

10:07.980 --> 10:10.499
Ronnie Petersen goes around
calling us the N-word

10:10.536 --> 10:13.838
and burning crosses,
but somehow I'm the hothead?

10:15.868 --> 10:17.306
I'm out.

10:23.381 --> 10:26.388
EASY: Okay. So, we're, um...

10:26.666 --> 10:28.548
we're tracking down Detective Falcone's

10:28.585 --> 10:30.505
witnesses in your case.

10:35.262 --> 10:36.474
[CLEARS THROAT]

10:36.573 --> 10:37.943
First thing I do when I get out

10:37.980 --> 10:39.450
is I'm gonna have these removed.

10:39.487 --> 10:41.932
- I hear it's painful.
- Good.

10:42.172 --> 10:43.847
I deserve it.

10:46.129 --> 10:48.504
You know, it's crazy, isn't it, just...

10:48.613 --> 10:50.101
how all this hate over nothing

10:50.138 --> 10:52.052
can literally tear a country apart?

10:52.153 --> 10:54.071
What we don't understand, we fear.

10:54.802 --> 10:57.810
And fear and isolation breed
hatred, and...

10:58.596 --> 11:00.557
hatred roots in people.

11:01.395 --> 11:03.006
I think you're right.

11:03.730 --> 11:04.882
Here I am,

11:04.919 --> 11:06.376
just sitting here with you,

11:06.413 --> 11:08.823
normal as can be. [CHUCKLES]

11:08.863 --> 11:10.170
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

11:10.765 --> 11:13.917
15 years ago,
I couldn't even imagine this.

11:17.266 --> 11:18.849
You know, the key to your case

11:18.886 --> 11:20.571
is proving the witnesses lied.

11:20.608 --> 11:23.847
So... tell me about your alibi.

11:24.151 --> 11:25.879
It's disgusting.

11:26.547 --> 11:29.398
I was about two hours
away from that synagogue.

11:29.933 --> 11:32.371
Soaking burlap in Klan cologne.

11:32.649 --> 11:34.569
Getting everything ready
for a cross burning

11:34.606 --> 11:36.238
we were gonna do that night.

11:36.768 --> 11:38.008
Sounds like there were a lot of people

11:38.044 --> 11:39.840
who could vouch for you.

11:40.230 --> 11:42.230
Why didn't they?

11:44.256 --> 11:46.664
Most of them had records.

11:47.621 --> 11:49.535
And everyone knew that Falcone
was gonna be framing me,

11:49.596 --> 11:51.279
so they was just glad it wasn't them.

11:51.316 --> 11:52.699
We only need one.

11:53.603 --> 11:54.662
Mm.

11:54.699 --> 11:57.108
Well, I did have a
girlfriend at that time.

11:57.145 --> 11:59.152
So, if we find her,
do you think she'll help?

11:59.212 --> 12:00.436
I don't know.

12:00.473 --> 12:03.363
As I remember it,
she was pretty hateful back then, too.

12:04.526 --> 12:07.160
Hmm. All right.

12:07.886 --> 12:09.888
<i>Bodie tracked down one
of those false witnesses,</i>

12:09.908 --> 12:12.391
Dante Jordan, and he's on
the streets finding him now.

12:12.735 --> 12:14.706
Levi? Why are you here?

12:15.078 --> 12:16.661
Hey, sis.

12:17.029 --> 12:18.420
[MADELINE SIGHS]

12:18.494 --> 12:21.511
- What?
- I found Toby Kissell.

12:21.691 --> 12:23.779
You said that there was an
Adderall ring in high school,

12:23.816 --> 12:25.536
right, that-that Rosemary
was secretly taking...

12:25.573 --> 12:27.293
that Toby was the guy that
was selling the Adderall?

12:27.329 --> 12:29.771
- So?
- So maybe that's why he killed her.

12:29.808 --> 12:31.370
YOUNG TOBY: <i>Cheers. Come on, drink up.</i>

12:31.495 --> 12:33.505
- Come on. Finish the whole...
- [LAUGHS] Don't rush me.

12:33.542 --> 12:35.003
- Come on. Cheers.
- [LAUGHS]: Oh!

12:35.040 --> 12:36.056
LEVI: <i>What if he was her dealer?</i>

12:36.093 --> 12:37.099
You know,
then he's hooking up with her?

12:37.136 --> 12:39.287
Then he lies about us at our trial?

12:39.324 --> 12:40.861
YOUNG TOBY: <i>Levi went berserk</i>

12:41.042 --> 12:44.177
<i>after he caught me and
Rosemary in the tent kissing.</i>

12:44.214 --> 12:46.129
<i>He said that he was mad at Rosemary,</i>

12:46.166 --> 12:48.160
that he wanted to kill that bitch.

12:48.811 --> 12:50.338
BELLOWS: <i>Nothing further.</i>

12:50.558 --> 12:51.750
LEVI: <i>He lied about us.</i>

12:51.795 --> 12:54.109
I mean, why would he say
something like that in court

12:54.146 --> 12:55.624
unless he was trying to hide something?

12:55.682 --> 12:57.749
- Huh?
- [SIGHS]

13:00.873 --> 13:02.623
All right.

13:03.029 --> 13:04.625
Yeah. There could be something there.

13:04.743 --> 13:06.357
- We should talk to him.
- Okay, good. I found him.

13:06.394 --> 13:08.563
He's-he's living in Evanston.
I say we go there now.

13:08.600 --> 13:10.734
I can't today.
I have a case I'm dealing with.

13:10.771 --> 13:13.029
[SIGHS] Okay, fine.
I'm heading up there myself, then.

13:13.084 --> 13:15.188
'Cause, sis, I'm gonna prove to you

13:15.287 --> 13:17.032
I did not kill her.

13:21.713 --> 13:23.224
[SIGHS]

13:27.280 --> 13:29.255
Oh!

13:29.529 --> 13:30.966
Toby Kissell?

13:31.089 --> 13:34.037
[CHUCKLES] Almost didn't
recognize you there.

13:34.156 --> 13:35.733
- Hey, Levi, uh...
- Hey.

13:36.001 --> 13:37.569
What are you... doing around here?

13:37.632 --> 13:39.375
Oh, I'm looking for you.

13:40.783 --> 13:43.880
What's it been... like, 17 years?

13:44.920 --> 13:46.876
- Yeah?
- What can I, uh, do for you?

13:46.998 --> 13:49.107
I'm just tracking down old
friends, you know.

13:49.377 --> 13:51.944
I mean, we-we are old friends, right?

13:52.531 --> 13:53.649
Yeah. Sure.

13:53.686 --> 13:56.726
All that trial stuff is
water under the bridge?

13:56.763 --> 13:58.698
Well, aside from the ten
years that my sister and I

13:58.775 --> 14:00.091
spent in prison, yeah, sure.

14:00.128 --> 14:01.569
Yeah, well, I-I should go.

14:01.763 --> 14:03.843
Hey, tell me something, Toby...
what-what have you been doing

14:03.879 --> 14:05.262
with the last ten years
of your life, huh?

14:05.299 --> 14:07.690
You got, like, a wife,
you have family, kids?

14:07.959 --> 14:09.709
Uh, I'm divorced. No kids.

14:09.828 --> 14:11.861
Wow. That's a shame.

14:11.960 --> 14:14.085
You were, like,
top dog in high school, you know?

14:14.165 --> 14:15.773
Different girl every week.

14:15.922 --> 14:17.812
Slinging Adderall to all the kids.

14:17.849 --> 14:19.552
- I sell insurance now.
- Ooh.

14:19.671 --> 14:21.265
Anyway, I, uh... I should go.

14:21.302 --> 14:22.726
We should talk. We should catch up,

14:22.763 --> 14:24.115
you know, about old times.

14:24.199 --> 14:25.807
I don't know, like,
maybe like what happened

14:25.844 --> 14:27.969
the night that Rosemary
Lynch got murdered.

14:28.045 --> 14:30.788
Everybody's moved on from that.
It was a long time ago.

14:30.816 --> 14:32.348
Yeah, except for when
you're sitting in jail

14:32.385 --> 14:33.625
for a crime you didn't commit.

14:33.652 --> 14:35.989
Then time just kind of stands
still, Toby.

14:36.026 --> 14:38.541
I keep replaying that-that
night over and over again

14:38.578 --> 14:40.357
in my mind,
and I-I can't quite figure out

14:40.450 --> 14:42.811
why you lied on the stand.
Did you kill her?

14:42.848 --> 14:43.850
- Huh?
- What?

14:43.887 --> 14:45.087
Was it because of the Adderall ring?

14:45.124 --> 14:47.084
- Because she was gonna expose you?
- No, of course I didn't.

14:47.120 --> 14:49.304
- Did you kill her?
- Stay the hell away from me!

14:49.541 --> 14:51.816
[HORN HONKS]

14:54.030 --> 14:55.278
ALDERS: <i>This is our first debate</i>

14:55.315 --> 14:57.498
in the race for Illinois
attorney general.

14:57.674 --> 15:00.871
On my right is Cook County
State's Attorney Gore Bellows.

15:00.908 --> 15:02.643
- [APPLAUSE]
- On my left,

15:02.680 --> 15:04.793
former prosecutor Evan Esteban-Miller.

15:04.830 --> 15:06.713
- Welcome to you both.
- [CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

15:06.916 --> 15:08.768
Our first question is for Mr. Bellows.

15:08.971 --> 15:11.174
Voters believe that police misconduct

15:11.211 --> 15:13.062
is still a major concern.

15:13.191 --> 15:15.322
If elected attorney general,

15:15.359 --> 15:17.502
how will you address this issue?

15:17.529 --> 15:19.504
I think transparency is the key.

15:19.740 --> 15:21.263
I plan to implement several programs

15:21.324 --> 15:23.708
both for citizens and for the police,

15:23.786 --> 15:25.125
whose lives are still being sacrificed

15:25.162 --> 15:26.619
on our streets every day.

15:26.738 --> 15:30.457
But more importantly,
it will rebuild the trust

15:30.575 --> 15:33.153
between the community and
the police department.

15:33.214 --> 15:36.550
Because a relationship
can't survive without trust.

15:36.707 --> 15:38.456
[APPLAUSE]

15:40.019 --> 15:42.694
Mr. Esteban-Miller, same question.

15:43.128 --> 15:44.286
Fact:

15:44.323 --> 15:46.919
last year over 6,000
complaints were filed

15:46.956 --> 15:48.761
against the police in Chicago,

15:48.866 --> 15:50.459
but only two percent

15:50.520 --> 15:53.628
resulted in disciplinary action
for the officers involved

15:53.738 --> 15:55.279
under the office of Attorney Bellows.

15:55.316 --> 15:57.007
Yes, let's-let's blame that on
me, too. I mean,

15:57.044 --> 15:58.798
- that-that's entirely bogus.
- 98 to two,

15:58.835 --> 15:59.915
- it's clear which side -
Police disciplinary action

15:59.951 --> 16:01.512
- Attorney Bellows is on.
- has nothing to do...

16:01.548 --> 16:02.827
As attorney general, I plan to work

16:02.864 --> 16:04.447
with the police unions and the city

16:04.484 --> 16:06.449
to modify policies so that we can flip

16:06.486 --> 16:07.576
those numbers.

16:07.613 --> 16:10.755
Because transparency isn't just key.

16:10.876 --> 16:12.889
It's often a matter of life and death.

16:12.951 --> 16:14.542
[CHEERING]

16:16.412 --> 16:17.616
ISABEL: <i>I think it went well.</i>

16:17.653 --> 16:18.889
That's 'cause you're an idiot.

16:18.926 --> 16:20.313
You weren't prepared.

16:20.350 --> 16:22.157
Now maybe you'll
listen to me next time.

16:22.235 --> 16:24.467
Holy wow, Gore. That was mediocre.

16:24.529 --> 16:25.811
What did you say to my husband?

16:25.885 --> 16:27.203
Oh, that he's a train wreck.

16:27.240 --> 16:28.656
Yeah, you got to come out guns blazing

16:28.693 --> 16:30.844
to change the narrative. It was bad.

16:30.881 --> 16:33.168
Thank you, Susan. That's enough.

16:33.500 --> 16:34.857
Ugh.

16:42.011 --> 16:43.152
Dante Jordan?

16:43.209 --> 16:44.272
Bodie Quick.

16:44.309 --> 16:46.090
I'm with the Injustice Defense Group.

16:46.343 --> 16:48.686
Look, we need to talk to
you about Ronnie Petersen.

16:49.305 --> 16:51.305
Aw, I'm wearing the wrong shoes.

16:59.422 --> 17:00.755
[GRUNTS]

17:15.334 --> 17:17.318
[PHONE RINGS]

17:19.560 --> 17:20.690
Hey.

17:20.727 --> 17:23.069
I think the word is out that
we're going after Falcone.

17:24.347 --> 17:26.722
[SIGHS] Yeah.

17:28.588 --> 17:30.116
I know.

17:30.787 --> 17:32.245
Well?

17:32.592 --> 17:34.806
- Message sent.
- Good.

17:35.237 --> 17:37.762
Appreciate you looking out.

17:46.034 --> 17:47.530
[SIGHS]

17:50.252 --> 17:51.918
What's Detective Falcone got on
you, buddy?

17:51.955 --> 17:53.421
No idea what you're talking about, man.

17:53.458 --> 17:54.718
Come on. Six trials, you told

17:54.755 --> 17:56.115
the jury exactly what Detective Falcone

17:56.151 --> 17:57.126
wanted you to say.

17:57.163 --> 17:59.237
That's perjury. You can go to
jail for a long time for that.

17:59.274 --> 18:00.436
What do you want from me, man?

18:00.473 --> 18:02.483
15 years ago,
the Ronnie Petersen trial,

18:02.520 --> 18:04.928
you gave false testimony.
Falcone paid you to do it.

18:04.970 --> 18:06.854
Now we need you to tell the judge that.

18:07.014 --> 18:08.781
No, man. No, man. Look, he... look,

18:08.936 --> 18:11.217
h-he doesn't even pay me anymore, man.
He doesn't pay me.

18:11.254 --> 18:13.134
He just threatens to lock me
up if I don't do what he wants.

18:13.208 --> 18:15.178
Right. Well, we're taking Falcone down.

18:15.264 --> 18:17.123
You want the threats to end?

18:17.256 --> 18:18.744
You got to help us out.

18:22.553 --> 18:24.964
Well, this is a very
well-written puff piece.

18:25.569 --> 18:27.967
It's absolutely wonderful
in its frivolity.

18:28.069 --> 18:30.366
- Come on. I mean, it's not that bad.
- Oh, it's bad.

18:30.403 --> 18:32.210
I can't print this.

18:32.247 --> 18:33.874
But I can find another writer.

18:33.911 --> 18:35.248
Hey, just... Don't do that.

18:35.285 --> 18:37.006
Just let me keep going, okay?

18:37.043 --> 18:39.905
- I will get you something.
- You better.

18:40.264 --> 18:42.064
Or someone else will.

18:43.507 --> 18:44.956
[SIGHS]

18:52.777 --> 18:54.405
BODIE: Hiya. I got Dante Jordan

18:54.442 --> 18:55.831
to agree to testify.

18:56.050 --> 18:57.857
That's great. Uh...

18:57.894 --> 18:59.105
I found Ronnie's ex-girlfriend.

18:59.142 --> 19:00.558
She confirms his alibi.

19:00.667 --> 19:02.003
How'd you get Dante to step forward?

19:02.040 --> 19:04.245
Falcone stiffed him for his
last two court appearances,

19:04.282 --> 19:06.925
and hell hath no fury like
a false witness scorned.

19:07.503 --> 19:08.950
See ya. Hey.

19:08.987 --> 19:10.568
- Hey.
- Vi.

19:10.595 --> 19:11.667
You're leaving?

19:11.704 --> 19:13.137
No goodbye?

19:16.120 --> 19:17.819
I heard about that bullet.

19:17.894 --> 19:19.636
Trying to get your head blown off, too?

19:19.761 --> 19:22.152
Okay. You know what? I get it.

19:22.206 --> 19:23.693
You're morally opposed to this case,

19:23.730 --> 19:25.152
and I understand why.

19:25.189 --> 19:27.769
It's horrible.
But I really can't take this attitude.

19:27.816 --> 19:29.583
We need to win, all right?

19:29.620 --> 19:31.763
So get on or get off or
whatever you need to do,

19:31.800 --> 19:33.745
but this train is moving.

19:39.457 --> 19:41.040
[SIGHS]

19:41.159 --> 19:42.675
[EXHALES]

19:49.667 --> 19:50.791
Take one.

19:50.995 --> 19:52.777
Not for air. Yet.

19:52.847 --> 19:57.816
I was one of a few black
kids at my high school.

19:57.956 --> 19:59.068
And one day,

19:59.105 --> 20:00.636
a few of us went to our lockers

20:00.673 --> 20:04.417
and found a noose hanging inside.

20:05.305 --> 20:08.234
<i>And our principal told us
that while it was awful,</i>

20:08.319 --> 20:10.312
racism was just a part of life

20:10.349 --> 20:12.226
that we needed to accept.

20:13.328 --> 20:14.556
<i>He said</i>

20:14.718 --> 20:16.508
the hate train

20:16.545 --> 20:18.664
was never gonna <i>come to a stop.</i>

20:19.846 --> 20:22.546
And we were just gonna
have to toughen up...

20:24.810 --> 20:27.753
and ride it out like
everyone else in history.

20:29.525 --> 20:32.468
Have you ever had to ride that train?

20:33.554 --> 20:34.703
MAN: <i>So, remember,</i>

20:34.740 --> 20:37.649
continue to do the Lord's
work and walk in his path.

20:37.734 --> 20:39.840
Thank you for coming,
and see you next week.

20:39.959 --> 20:41.768
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

20:42.226 --> 20:44.101
You need to talk to your son.

20:44.273 --> 20:46.255
Something happened to
him at school today.

20:46.335 --> 20:47.780
What happened?

20:48.093 --> 20:49.758
Audra and I will wait outside.

20:50.436 --> 20:52.520
Come on, baby.

20:56.906 --> 20:58.359
What happened at school?

20:58.435 --> 21:01.120
- I got into a fight.
- Over what?

21:01.375 --> 21:03.377
Kids was messing with
me about your case.

21:03.414 --> 21:06.033
I told you to fight with your
words, not your fists.

21:06.110 --> 21:07.794
You let that stuff roll off your back.

21:07.912 --> 21:09.470
And you don't have to
get yourself in trouble

21:09.507 --> 21:10.704
defending me.

21:10.823 --> 21:12.356
I was not defending you.

21:12.429 --> 21:13.887
I was defending myself.

21:13.960 --> 21:15.450
[SCOFFS]

21:15.727 --> 21:17.310
You're a hypocrite, Dad.

21:18.089 --> 21:20.822
Always preaching pro-black this

21:20.859 --> 21:21.939
and Black Lives Matter that,

21:21.976 --> 21:23.609
but, man, you ain't really down.

21:23.819 --> 21:25.902
You told me to never compromise.

21:26.574 --> 21:28.224
And look at you.

21:28.632 --> 21:30.341
[SIGHS]

21:31.111 --> 21:32.632
Michael.

21:33.968 --> 21:36.547
One day you'll understand
why I'm doing this.

21:37.218 --> 21:39.113
I'll never understand this.

21:42.369 --> 21:44.470
It's for the greater good, son.

21:46.025 --> 21:47.408
Look at me.

21:48.096 --> 21:49.980
If you don't hear nothing else,

21:50.637 --> 21:52.078
hear that.

21:53.763 --> 21:55.697
All right, let's go home now.

21:59.987 --> 22:02.279
I, uh, got suspended.

22:06.031 --> 22:08.521
All right.
I'll talk to Principal Denton.

22:08.770 --> 22:09.969
I'll take care of it.

22:10.006 --> 22:11.230
Don't trip.

22:11.360 --> 22:12.634
Mom knows.

22:12.671 --> 22:14.221
She'll take it from here.

22:26.382 --> 22:27.523
[ATTICUS WHINES]

22:28.506 --> 22:29.968
I'm not gonna become
one of those people

22:30.005 --> 22:31.433
who talks to their dog, so...

22:31.573 --> 22:33.482
- [WHINES]
- You shut up.

22:33.941 --> 22:35.899
[KNOCKING AT DOOR]

22:38.819 --> 22:40.243
[ATTICUS GROWLS QUIETLY]

22:40.302 --> 22:41.635
Stay.

22:45.446 --> 22:47.538
- [KNOCKING]
- DYLAN: Hey.

22:50.209 --> 22:51.608
[EXHALES] Hey.

22:51.722 --> 22:53.186
Yeah. Uh...

22:53.987 --> 22:55.538
DYLAN [SOFTLY]: Hi.

22:55.655 --> 22:57.464
What a good boy, Atticus.

22:59.374 --> 23:01.581
[SIGHS]: Uh...

23:02.131 --> 23:04.468
listen, I think it's
pretty obvious that we...

23:05.045 --> 23:06.788
haven't been entirely
honest with each other.

23:06.825 --> 23:08.140
I'm sorry, th-there's just...
there's been...

23:08.176 --> 23:09.692
No, no, no, don't... don't apologize.

23:09.729 --> 23:11.366
I should have told you
this a long time ago.

23:11.514 --> 23:12.944
The truth is...

23:15.911 --> 23:18.897
I liked you since before
Becky and I broke up.

23:19.069 --> 23:20.154
[DYLAN SIGHS]

23:20.191 --> 23:22.187
I think you're inspiring...

23:23.681 --> 23:25.280
and smart

23:26.280 --> 23:27.866
and good.

23:28.910 --> 23:33.063
And I love your smile and
your eyes and your hair.

23:33.100 --> 23:36.971
And I get it, it's not easy
to be vulnerable for anybody.

23:37.089 --> 23:38.491
It's got to be even harder for you

23:38.528 --> 23:41.079
after everything that
you've gone through, but...

23:41.324 --> 23:44.917
but I want to try to do this, for real.

23:46.179 --> 23:48.955
If you want to... if you want to try.

23:50.640 --> 23:52.124
Do you want to?

23:54.061 --> 23:55.493
Yeah.

23:56.323 --> 23:57.954
I think I do.

23:59.192 --> 24:02.389
♪ ♪

24:07.405 --> 24:09.456
Hey, pretty girl.

24:09.530 --> 24:11.477
Back so soon?

24:12.093 --> 24:13.368
We have a case that's causing

24:13.405 --> 24:16.761
some friction with Violet...
I need someone to talk to.

24:17.022 --> 24:19.558
What about that guy you
were telling me about?

24:20.942 --> 24:23.398
How come I don't see you for
months, and then the moment

24:23.435 --> 24:26.403
I lay eyes on you it
all comes flooding back?

24:28.702 --> 24:30.904
It's the same for me.

24:30.981 --> 24:32.890
So, I mean, tell me about this guy.

24:33.006 --> 24:34.922
- You still talking?
- Yeah.

24:34.959 --> 24:36.239
[CLEARS THROAT] Yeah, we're talking.

24:36.275 --> 24:37.507
He's around.

24:37.607 --> 24:39.148
Where's your girl?

24:40.205 --> 24:42.539
- She's around.
- [CHUCKLES]

24:48.288 --> 24:50.582
MADELINE: <i>I want you to know
that, whoever I'm with,</i>

24:51.053 --> 24:53.400
<i>that a part of you is</i> always with me.

24:57.057 --> 24:58.891
I love you.

25:07.827 --> 25:09.267
MADELINE: All right,
so, we should tell you

25:09.303 --> 25:10.949
how this is gonna go
once we get inside.

25:10.986 --> 25:13.326
All right, listen, brother,
just tell the truth.

25:14.647 --> 25:16.327
You still good to go, man?

25:18.358 --> 25:19.545
DANTE: Hell, yeah.

25:19.663 --> 25:21.092
I'm tired of his corrupt ass, man.

25:21.181 --> 25:22.847
- Let's do this.
- [SIRENS WAILING]

25:27.296 --> 25:29.060
- Dante Jordan, you're under arrest.
- For what?

25:29.105 --> 25:30.133
What the h...

25:30.170 --> 25:31.236
- what the hell's going on, man?
- MADELINE: Hey! Excuse me.

25:31.272 --> 25:32.719
I'm his lawyer. What's the charge?

25:32.785 --> 25:34.097
Here's the arrest warrant.

25:34.249 --> 25:35.786
Hey, what's going on, man?

25:36.558 --> 25:37.998
You said I was good.

25:38.271 --> 25:39.886
MADELINE: <i>We can't proceed, Your Honor.</i>

25:39.959 --> 25:41.959
Our witness, Dante
Jordan, was just arrested.

25:41.986 --> 25:43.914
- On the courthouse steps.
- That's unfortunate.

25:43.951 --> 25:45.951
It's criminal.
The prosecution knew that

25:45.988 --> 25:47.872
Mr. Jordan was about to testify

25:47.909 --> 25:49.149
to the threats and the corruption

25:49.186 --> 25:51.135
that Detective Falcone
used in this case.

25:51.172 --> 25:53.395
- They're protecting Falcone.
- Mr. Duncan,

25:53.470 --> 25:54.910
- what's going on here?
- Sorry, Your Honor,

25:54.946 --> 25:56.307
I'm just getting caught up.

25:56.344 --> 25:58.840
I was recently given a
copy of an arrest warrant

25:58.877 --> 25:59.973
for Dante Jordan.

26:00.010 --> 26:03.255
Armed robbery,
felony assault of a peace officer.

26:03.374 --> 26:04.573
From what I gather,
the police have been looking

26:04.592 --> 26:06.166
- for him for some time.
- And they just

26:06.324 --> 26:09.009
happen to make an arrest right
before he was about to testify?

26:09.046 --> 26:10.646
- Guess they knew where to find him.
- Your Honor,

26:10.683 --> 26:12.125
it's an obvious attempt
to keep our witness

26:12.162 --> 26:14.161
from exposing the corruption
of Detective Falcone.

26:14.327 --> 26:16.977
The prosecution's playing
dirty to protect a dirty cop.

26:17.054 --> 26:19.350
Do you have any evidence to
substantiate these allegations?

26:19.387 --> 26:21.287
I did. He just got arrested.

26:21.324 --> 26:23.092
We need a continuance, Your Honor.

26:23.240 --> 26:25.169
Fine. Get your ducks in a row.

26:25.196 --> 26:26.721
We do this again in two days.

26:26.799 --> 26:28.584
Court's adjourned.

26:29.201 --> 26:31.867
- What the hell just happened?
- A slight delay.

26:34.039 --> 26:35.422
You just play me, boy?

26:35.490 --> 26:36.938
Oh, that's right, I see you, brother.

26:36.958 --> 26:38.177
- OFFICER: Let's go.
- What's up?

26:38.214 --> 26:41.031
- [SCOFFS] I see you, brother.
- Come on. Move.

26:43.658 --> 26:45.466
What the hell was that?

26:45.580 --> 26:48.295
Looks like our leopard
still has his spots.

26:52.445 --> 26:53.775
EASY: <i>It was that look.</i>

26:53.812 --> 26:54.978
You know what I'm talking about.

26:55.015 --> 26:56.533
So I was right... he was conning us.

26:56.808 --> 26:59.168
- Can we drop this case?
- No. We can't give up.

26:59.205 --> 27:01.212
We have one shot at Falcone.
This is it.

27:01.249 --> 27:03.223
Even though he is clearly a racist.

27:03.423 --> 27:05.187
BODIE: Well,
we've got another huge problem.

27:05.226 --> 27:06.783
Our star witness is
in the county lockup

27:06.828 --> 27:07.947
for the foreseeable future,

27:07.984 --> 27:09.864
which means he's
definitely not testifying.

27:09.901 --> 27:11.446
Then we need to find a different angle.

27:11.632 --> 27:13.072
All right, 30-year career, Falcone

27:13.109 --> 27:15.257
leaned on dozens of people.
He must have had help.

27:15.328 --> 27:16.451
You mean other cops.

27:16.488 --> 27:18.049
VIOLET: Even if he had
help, there is no way

27:18.086 --> 27:19.621
his brothers in blue
are gonna flip on him.

27:19.953 --> 27:22.092
Unless we can force them to.

27:22.217 --> 27:23.292
Let's see who we can leverage.

27:23.329 --> 27:24.869
Work your contacts.
Someone on the inside

27:24.906 --> 27:26.137
must have hated Falcone

27:26.174 --> 27:28.424
- just as mu...
- Much as I hate our client?

27:32.994 --> 27:34.499
[DOOR OPENS]

27:34.847 --> 27:37.289
RECEPTIONIST: Can I help you? Sir.

27:37.635 --> 27:38.685
Toby Kissell?

27:39.310 --> 27:40.568
What are you doing here?

27:40.605 --> 27:42.656
Keep your drug-addicted
brother away from me.

27:44.328 --> 27:46.103
Look, I don't know what
Levi said to you...

27:46.140 --> 27:48.299
He accused me of killing Rosemary,

27:48.336 --> 27:50.973
which is ridiculous...
we all know who really killed her.

27:51.010 --> 27:52.425
Do we?

27:53.139 --> 27:55.984
Because the way I remember it,
you blatantly lied on the stand.

27:56.021 --> 27:57.234
That's perjury, and it makes

27:57.271 --> 27:58.345
- you look pretty guilty.
- No.

27:58.382 --> 28:00.055
I testified to what I heard.

28:00.092 --> 28:01.804
You lied, and we both know it.

28:01.841 --> 28:03.569
If I see him again,
I'm calling the cops.

28:03.648 --> 28:05.808
He's messed up.
I don't want him anywhere near me.

28:06.539 --> 28:08.820
Because he reminds you
of how guilty you are?

28:09.117 --> 28:11.703
Or because you stole ten years from us?

28:11.984 --> 28:13.429
No, don't look away.

28:13.612 --> 28:15.226
You look me in the eye, and you tell me

28:15.263 --> 28:17.132
that you think Levi killed her.

28:18.350 --> 28:20.016
Exactly.

28:20.561 --> 28:22.621
What else are you hiding, Toby?

28:23.046 --> 28:25.122
Don't you come in here like
you're the innocent victim,

28:25.149 --> 28:26.457
because you're not.

28:26.484 --> 28:29.068
You ruined him.

28:29.228 --> 28:31.672
You're a coward and you're pathetic,

28:31.709 --> 28:33.405
and everything that happened to him

28:33.442 --> 28:34.990
is <i> your</i> fault.

28:36.193 --> 28:38.327
Get out of my office.

28:49.252 --> 28:52.131
I think you're putting a spell
on me with all this good food.

28:52.168 --> 28:53.276
Mmm.

28:53.346 --> 28:54.668
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

28:55.153 --> 28:56.894
Does it make you want
to sleep with me more?

28:56.931 --> 29:00.408
Mm. Makes me crush on you more.

29:01.292 --> 29:02.433
Yeah?

29:02.470 --> 29:04.207
- Yeah.
- Finally.

29:05.103 --> 29:06.847
Does this mean that we can...

29:06.965 --> 29:10.338
go out in public and have
dinner in a restaurant?

29:10.510 --> 29:12.519
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

29:13.306 --> 29:15.155
Okay, but nothing fancy.

29:16.838 --> 29:18.358
I promise take you to
the most mediocre place

29:18.607 --> 29:19.691
- I can find.
- Yeah?

29:19.728 --> 29:21.185
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

29:21.622 --> 29:23.455
Hey, if we go public,

29:23.717 --> 29:26.670
I need you to stop trying to
free the white supremacists.

29:26.793 --> 29:29.295
- [LAUGHS]
- He's a scumbag. Period.

29:30.089 --> 29:31.355
- Okay.
- Yeah.

29:31.589 --> 29:34.256
I guess Falcone did a good thing
putting him away, then, yeah?

29:34.293 --> 29:36.693
Falcone's a piece of crap.
He's one of the bad ones.

29:37.606 --> 29:39.120
You ever work with him?

29:39.685 --> 29:41.910
No, but, uh, his partner...

29:42.006 --> 29:43.390
"Dirty David" Moss...

29:43.427 --> 29:45.719
that guy used to hit on me nonstop.
He's a pig.

29:46.394 --> 29:47.638
You want me to take him out for you?

29:47.675 --> 29:49.295
- You know I'm a ninja.
- [LAUGHS]: Yeah?

29:49.332 --> 29:51.589
Part-time. Part-time. You know.
I have the outfit.

29:51.628 --> 29:53.794
Yeah, well, that guy took himself out.

29:53.831 --> 29:56.012
Oh, this is good. Really good, babe.

29:56.049 --> 29:57.496
What do you mean he took himself out?

29:57.533 --> 29:59.825
He went out on some
bogus disability charge

29:59.862 --> 30:00.973
a couple years ago...

30:01.010 --> 30:03.285
rumor is he still collects

30:03.339 --> 30:04.701
three-quarters of his salary,

30:04.738 --> 30:06.223
- tax-free.
- What a pig.

30:06.293 --> 30:08.650
Exactly. Cheers.

30:08.750 --> 30:10.964
- Cheers.
- Babe, this looks good.

30:11.265 --> 30:12.556
So good.

30:12.777 --> 30:13.949
BODIE: <i>I got a name.</i>

30:14.043 --> 30:15.107
David Moss.

30:15.144 --> 30:17.412
Supposedly dislocated
his shoulder in the line,

30:17.449 --> 30:19.684
but I have it on good
authority he's a liar.

30:19.721 --> 30:21.395
VIOLET: So a cop who's
defrauding the city

30:21.432 --> 30:23.586
by taking disability but
isn't actually injured...

30:23.648 --> 30:25.086
that's our big breakthrough?

30:25.179 --> 30:26.723
Why not?
That's all the leverage we need,

30:26.760 --> 30:27.894
if we can prove it.

30:27.996 --> 30:29.811
[PHONE RINGING]

30:30.520 --> 30:32.973
Hey. I got to go somewhere.

30:33.033 --> 30:34.347
You want to work out some aggression?

30:34.384 --> 30:36.509
I think I do. Let me grab my coat.

30:40.050 --> 30:41.383
All right...

30:41.722 --> 30:42.925
when are you two gonna make up?

30:42.962 --> 30:44.488
It's getting seriously
weird around here.

30:44.558 --> 30:47.184
Whenever she wants.
This is her thing, not mine.

30:47.245 --> 30:49.936
I know, it's awful,
but there's a bigger picture here.

30:49.973 --> 30:52.765
If we win, we can help a
lot of innocent people.

30:52.802 --> 30:54.669
Let's stay focused on that.

30:57.475 --> 30:58.867
[GRUNTS]

31:02.204 --> 31:03.787
Your weight.

31:06.287 --> 31:08.195
What did you just say to me?

31:08.352 --> 31:09.910
Your weight.

31:10.296 --> 31:12.559
You got to put your
weight back a little.

31:13.814 --> 31:15.900
Do you want to show me how to do it?

31:19.112 --> 31:21.784
Wow! Where have you been all my life?

31:21.852 --> 31:23.572
Do it again.

31:33.126 --> 31:34.884
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

31:34.997 --> 31:36.997
[DOOR BELLS JINGLE]

31:40.293 --> 31:41.851
MADELINE: David Moss?

31:42.608 --> 31:45.275
Hi. I'm Madeline Scott.

31:45.426 --> 31:46.850
I know who you are.

31:46.893 --> 31:50.056
EASY: You're receiving
$2,700 a month in disability.

31:50.478 --> 31:53.100
- Tax-free.
- Have been for the last five years.

31:53.525 --> 31:55.585
- Exercise is part of my rehab.
- EASY: Hmm.

31:55.647 --> 31:56.916
What the hell do you want?

31:56.953 --> 31:58.697
You want to serve your
time with dozens of men

31:58.734 --> 32:00.493
Falcone put behind bars unfairly?

32:00.530 --> 32:01.985
I'm sure they'd love to see you.

32:02.048 --> 32:03.611
I don't know what you're talking about.

32:03.648 --> 32:05.123
I'm not your guy.

32:05.705 --> 32:07.056
Okay.

32:07.689 --> 32:10.819
That is the number to the
chair of the Disability Review.

32:11.150 --> 32:14.116
- [LINE RINGING]
- I'll just give him a call.

32:16.709 --> 32:18.042
Up to you, David.

32:18.657 --> 32:20.447
Food's better here, though.

32:20.701 --> 32:22.201
Trust me, I know.

32:23.455 --> 32:24.776
WOMAN: <i>Hello. You've reached the chair</i>

32:24.812 --> 32:26.010
<i>of the Disability Review.</i>

32:26.047 --> 32:27.556
Hang up right now.

32:31.212 --> 32:33.353
You want me to flip on Falcone?

32:33.928 --> 32:36.262
He was my partner for
11 and a half years.

32:36.353 --> 32:38.578
If he goes down,
you're gonna take me down with him.

32:38.979 --> 32:40.862
MADELINE: You don't have a choice.

32:43.544 --> 32:46.573
Okay. But I don't do
anything without immunity.

32:50.509 --> 32:51.923
All right, this is very tricky.

32:51.960 --> 32:54.052
We can apply. We probably won't get it.

32:54.089 --> 32:56.256
Bellows is the only sure
way to get him immunity.

32:56.293 --> 32:58.653
Moss is perfect,
and we've got him nailed.

32:59.041 --> 33:01.377
There's got to be another
way to get him to testify.

33:02.731 --> 33:04.397
[SIGHS]

33:07.885 --> 33:09.510
[INDISTINCT CHATTER IN DISTANCE]

33:11.910 --> 33:13.451
- [COMPUTER CHIMES]
- WOMAN: You're welcome.

33:15.455 --> 33:17.176
VIOLET: <i>You want to know
what happened to those kids</i>

33:17.212 --> 33:18.429
<i>who hung the noose in our lockers?</i>

33:18.466 --> 33:19.649
<i>Not a damn thing.</i>

33:20.422 --> 33:23.162
<i>They got off with an insincere apology.</i>

33:24.344 --> 33:26.088
The Ronnie Petersens of this world...

33:26.125 --> 33:27.440
they have a contagious disease.

33:27.477 --> 33:28.859
It's called hatred.

33:29.316 --> 33:31.293
This is my cross to bear.

33:31.414 --> 33:34.248
<i>So if you don't like my attitude,</i>

33:34.568 --> 33:36.676
<i>be a real friend and try to understand</i>

33:36.713 --> 33:40.006
<i>why I even have one in the first place.</i>

33:40.208 --> 33:41.713
- [CLICKS]
- I thought about putting that

33:41.750 --> 33:43.707
up on the podcast,

33:44.438 --> 33:47.956
but then I realized it was
just intended for one person.

33:48.356 --> 33:50.281
I'm so sorry, Vi.

33:51.049 --> 33:54.316
My tunnel vision in this case
is not an excuse to be a jerk,

33:54.353 --> 33:56.090
especially to you.

33:57.674 --> 33:59.718
I wasn't thinking
about your experience.

33:59.838 --> 34:02.672
Probably because I don't
really know enough about it.

34:02.699 --> 34:04.616
Well, it doesn't exactly come up

34:04.653 --> 34:06.703
in everyday conversation, does it?

34:07.408 --> 34:10.103
I want you to know you can tell
me anything any time you want.

34:10.315 --> 34:11.588
I'll hear you.

34:12.429 --> 34:15.275
For today, is there any
chance I could get, like,

34:15.337 --> 34:17.775
a one-time idiot friend pass?

34:17.856 --> 34:19.464
There is,

34:19.501 --> 34:21.777
- but it expires.
- That's fair.

34:22.016 --> 34:23.635
Hmm.

34:23.946 --> 34:26.286
- I love you.
- I love you.

34:26.626 --> 34:30.197
So, you're gonna want to hug me again,

34:30.235 --> 34:32.636
because I had a hunch,
and I went through

34:32.672 --> 34:35.118
Falcone's IAD complaints.

34:35.628 --> 34:37.139
Look at that.

34:41.797 --> 34:43.337
That's an ugly way to go.

34:43.373 --> 34:44.739
It's an ugly case.

34:49.626 --> 34:51.150
They made three major drug busts

34:51.187 --> 34:52.222
- today alone.
- Mm.

34:52.259 --> 34:54.313
It's a perfect way to change the story.
It's fantastic.

34:54.469 --> 34:55.946
Get it on the cover of the <i> Trib.</i>

34:55.983 --> 34:57.335
Then it's fantastic.

35:01.331 --> 35:02.595
Ah.

35:02.731 --> 35:04.231
Ms. Scott.

35:05.062 --> 35:06.261
What a surprise.

35:06.298 --> 35:07.591
Please, come in.

35:07.628 --> 35:08.931
VIOLET: <i>My parents always</i>

35:08.968 --> 35:12.461
taught me that nothing in life is free.

35:13.220 --> 35:16.020
That everything we
want comes at a price

35:16.376 --> 35:18.189
if we're willing to pay.

35:18.518 --> 35:21.634
That payment is what I call sacrifice.

35:23.126 --> 35:25.493
Let me get this straight.
[CLEARS THROAT]

35:26.015 --> 35:27.876
You want me to request immunity

35:27.939 --> 35:30.535
so that a white supremacist
can be set free?

35:31.295 --> 35:33.037
There's something in it for you, too.

35:33.908 --> 35:35.206
12 years ago, your opponent,

35:35.243 --> 35:36.946
Esteban-Miller, represented Falcone

35:36.983 --> 35:39.460
on a series of corruption
charges and won.

35:40.196 --> 35:42.251
He suborned perjury. It's a scandal.

35:42.392 --> 35:44.607
You grant Moss immunity, indict Falcone

35:44.634 --> 35:46.415
and score some big political points

35:46.452 --> 35:47.701
using it against your opponent.

35:48.259 --> 35:50.222
I thought this was your
candidate of choice.

35:50.259 --> 35:52.949
Please believe that if I'm here
it's because I'm out of options.

35:52.991 --> 35:54.839
And anyway, Esteban-Miller kept Falcone

35:54.876 --> 35:56.789
on the streets for years,
which means he's, in a way,

35:56.826 --> 35:59.559
responsible for dozens
of wrongful convictions.

36:01.239 --> 36:03.239
It's intriguing.

36:04.093 --> 36:05.775
I give you Falcone,

36:06.275 --> 36:08.072
you give me the headline
and the ammunition

36:08.442 --> 36:10.409
against Esteban-Miller.

36:12.747 --> 36:15.614
But Moss has to testify
on a different case.

36:15.660 --> 36:17.325
I cannot be responsible

36:17.378 --> 36:19.945
for getting a white
supremacist out of jail.

36:20.745 --> 36:22.478
Certainly not in an election year.

36:22.700 --> 36:24.311
MADELINE: <i>So,
he'll give us what we want.</i>

36:24.348 --> 36:27.741
We just have to get Moss to
testify in a different case.

36:27.914 --> 36:29.921
Bellows doesn't want to
see Petersen go free.

36:29.958 --> 36:31.912
This is perfect. We get to nail Falcone

36:31.949 --> 36:34.040
and we don't have to
free a Nazi to do it.

36:34.077 --> 36:35.535
That's fine by me.

36:36.234 --> 36:37.617
No.

36:38.044 --> 36:40.809
- I won't do it.
- Seriously?

36:40.888 --> 36:42.964
Whether Petersen is a racist or
not, we all know

36:43.001 --> 36:44.676
he didn't commit this crime.

36:45.890 --> 36:48.559
He deserves our defense
on that principle alone.

36:50.102 --> 36:51.973
I dedicated my life to
freeing the innocent.

36:52.010 --> 36:54.229
I'm not going to stop
now for a good deal

36:54.266 --> 36:55.932
or because I don't like the client.

36:56.366 --> 36:58.235
We're either wrongful
conviction attorneys

36:58.272 --> 37:00.180
or we're just like Falcone...

37:01.054 --> 37:03.375
making deals to get what we want.

37:11.345 --> 37:13.746
I offered to make the deal,

37:14.306 --> 37:16.737
but I will not release
a white supremacist,

37:16.774 --> 37:18.849
and Madeline's partner won't budge.

37:19.230 --> 37:21.730
So... make the deal.

37:21.767 --> 37:22.800
[BELLOWS SIGHS]

37:22.837 --> 37:24.816
It's a direct hit on Esteban-Miller,

37:24.853 --> 37:27.516
and the details about
Ronnie Petersen will be

37:27.553 --> 37:30.007
buried in a tidal wave
of Falcone's other cases.

37:30.044 --> 37:32.702
I'm not putting a Nazi
back on the streets.

37:32.826 --> 37:34.400
I still have a conscience.

37:34.494 --> 37:36.327
Who cares? He served 15 years.

37:36.445 --> 37:39.872
I care. I'm sick of making
compromises for this campaign.

37:39.909 --> 37:42.026
I got a job to do.
I'd like to keep doing it.

37:42.171 --> 37:43.466
[GRETA SIGHS]

37:47.467 --> 37:49.434
I had a miscarriage.

37:52.850 --> 37:54.833
What are you talking about?

37:55.339 --> 37:57.270
23 years ago.

37:58.222 --> 38:00.426
I never told you because...

38:00.917 --> 38:02.928
I didn't know if I wanted to keep it.

38:03.206 --> 38:04.878
I just wasn't sure...

38:06.128 --> 38:08.601
and then the decision was made for me.

38:08.933 --> 38:12.271
It happened right after
Isabel's mother was murdered.

38:12.706 --> 38:14.745
You were so upset
over that case that...

38:15.533 --> 38:16.743
I didn't want to pile on,

38:16.780 --> 38:19.206
so I kept the whole thing a secret.

38:20.482 --> 38:23.151
The way the press destroyed
you during that time...

38:24.323 --> 38:26.836
I'd cry at night, I was so angry.

38:28.528 --> 38:31.097
And I'm sure that's
why I lost the baby.

38:32.837 --> 38:34.218
Is that why you hate Isabel so much...

38:34.255 --> 38:35.863
because you blamed her?

38:36.282 --> 38:37.805
Maybe.

38:39.089 --> 38:41.617
Or maybe it was the fact
she became your baby.

38:41.816 --> 38:43.710
It just...

38:44.269 --> 38:45.925
it bothered me.

38:47.300 --> 38:50.126
And I know it's not fair to
her, but nah.

38:51.354 --> 38:53.546
I don't care.

38:57.991 --> 38:59.975
[BELLOWS SIGHS]

39:00.315 --> 39:02.464
I'm sorry you had to go through that.

39:02.838 --> 39:05.231
You should have told me.

39:06.690 --> 39:08.477
Life is tough,

39:08.792 --> 39:10.546
but we fight on.

39:12.462 --> 39:16.330
Now make the deal and shove it
down Esteban-Miller's throat.

39:16.510 --> 39:19.395
I don't care how we win,
but we're gonna win.

39:20.237 --> 39:21.956
You're gonna be A.G.

39:22.034 --> 39:23.682
and then you're gonna be governor.

39:23.800 --> 39:25.017
Get it done.

39:25.054 --> 39:26.495
<i>[APPLAUSE, CHEERING AND WHISTLING]</i>

39:27.206 --> 39:28.729
Earlier today,

39:29.063 --> 39:31.143
after a thorough and
swift investigation,

39:31.180 --> 39:33.734
my office indicted
Detective Rich Falcone

39:33.839 --> 39:37.184
on charges of corruption
and police misconduct.

39:37.221 --> 39:38.974
- [SIREN CHIRPS]
- I immediately took action

39:39.011 --> 39:40.612
<i>- and placed him under arrest</i>
- Falcone, hold up.

39:40.648 --> 39:42.870
<i>and have reopened</i> and
will personally review

39:42.907 --> 39:45.089
<i>every case that may
have been impacted by</i>

39:45.126 --> 39:46.854
<i>Detective Falcone's misdeeds.</i>

39:46.891 --> 39:48.163
<i>Let me assure the public</i>

39:48.206 --> 39:50.292
that while every one
of these injustices

39:50.329 --> 39:51.489
will be made right,

39:51.526 --> 39:53.473
the truly guilty will not go free.

39:53.510 --> 39:56.243
[APPLAUSE, CHEERING]

39:57.003 --> 39:58.495
This is the type of leadership

39:58.532 --> 40:01.307
I will bring to the
attorney general's office.

40:01.432 --> 40:03.706
Unlike Evan Esteban-Miller,

40:03.743 --> 40:05.167
who previously represented

40:05.204 --> 40:07.770
Detective Falcone on
corruption charges.

40:07.943 --> 40:09.333
So the voters have to ask themselves

40:09.361 --> 40:12.019
who do they want for the
next attorney general...

40:12.620 --> 40:14.672
someone who's in league with dirty cops

40:14.858 --> 40:16.432
or someone who puts them behind bars?

40:16.610 --> 40:17.948
[APPLAUSE, CHEERING]

40:18.077 --> 40:19.660
Thank you.

40:22.612 --> 40:24.731
This is usually our favorite part.

40:24.964 --> 40:26.330
This one just feels kind of...

40:26.449 --> 40:29.362
Crappy? Depressing?

40:29.448 --> 40:30.797
[MADELINE SIGHS]

40:31.237 --> 40:32.948
You kind of regretting it, too?

40:33.417 --> 40:35.284
A little bit.

40:35.687 --> 40:37.020
We had to do it.

40:38.253 --> 40:40.044
- Hey!
- Son.

40:40.081 --> 40:41.866
- How you doing?
- Okay.

40:42.147 --> 40:44.143
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

40:49.100 --> 40:50.993
So, what's it gonna be, Ronnie?

40:52.119 --> 40:54.338
You're all right with me, Easy.

41:13.032 --> 41:14.966
MADELINE: Take care.

41:18.951 --> 41:20.325
Why'd you do that?

41:21.613 --> 41:23.143
For the greater good.

41:23.995 --> 41:26.028
I just pray that small gesture did more

41:26.065 --> 41:28.774
than those gates did when
they opened up for him.

41:31.057 --> 41:32.375
VIOLET: <i>We all sacrificed</i>

41:32.402 --> 41:33.970
<i>a piece of ourselves</i>

41:34.404 --> 41:38.089
<i>to help right the wrongs of
a wicked and corrupt cop,</i>

41:38.720 --> 41:41.183
<i>and we did it because it
was the right thing to do</i>

41:41.261 --> 41:44.341
<i>for those men and women
who were powerless</i>

41:44.378 --> 41:47.281
<i>and who already paid
the ultimate price.</i>

41:47.518 --> 41:49.858
<i>This case tested us all.</i>

41:50.378 --> 41:52.597
It made some of us stronger,

41:54.143 --> 41:56.698
and some of us more conflicted,

41:56.971 --> 41:59.513
<i>but sometimes,
you have to make sacrifices</i>

41:59.550 --> 42:01.164
<i>to serve the greater good.</i>

42:01.201 --> 42:03.903
You played me, manipulated
me so I'd tell you about Moss

42:03.940 --> 42:05.331
